Yeah, I think those are using the `g_` prefix as well, see:

```
src/random.cpp:RNGState& GetRNGState() noexcept
src/random.cpp-{
src/random.cpp-    // This idiom relies on the guarantee that static variable are initialized
src/random.cpp-    // on first call, even when multiple parallel calls are permitted.
src/random.cpp-    static std::vector<RNGState, secure_allocator<RNGState>> g_rng(1);
src/random.cpp-    return g_rng[0];
src/random.cpp-}

